{
  "stem": "19837.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 30.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He could have worked as a furrier.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He-- they went to Australia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he came home one day, and he said, we can go to Australia if we leave now, immediately.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I-- When was this?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Huh?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was pregnant, so-- the boy was born in April, '38.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it must have been in end of '37.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said, I'm not going before that baby is born.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wanted my parents around if a boy-- you know, you have a bris milah, and I couldn't think of that without my father who had two daughters and wanted a boy so badly.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I said, I'm not leaving, and I want to have this baby right here, where your parents are, where my parents are.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's what we're going to do.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We stay till he's born, and then I promise, whatever we're going to do, we go.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When was your son born?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In April 8, '38-- 1938.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Berlin.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name is Henry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We gave him this name right away because we were-- knew we were going to leave Germany and we didn't want to give him a German name.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the only reason we could do that was that we were Czechoslovakian citizens, even we were both born in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father-in-law was Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's a long story.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then this-- the place where he was born became Czechoslovakian, so he had a Czechoslovakian passport, and the kids were all Czechoslovakian citizens.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the boys didn't really want to go into the Czech army, but they had to go say, we're ready to go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 68,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they weren't taken because they couldn't speak a word of Czech and they'd even never been there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 69,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when I married my husband, I lost my German citizenship and became a Czechoslovakian citizen.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
